"title": "8415: encouragement, examples of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8415: encouragement, examples of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Believers can encourage one another to have greater confidence in God and so to be bolder in living out their faith.</p>\n<h2>In the OT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:6-2Chr32:7\">2CH 32:6–32:7</a></strong> <em>King Hezekiah encourages his people.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:21-Judg20:22\">JDG 20:21–20:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam23:16\">1SA 23:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:10\">1CH 11:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:22\">2CH 30:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:2\">2CH 35:2</a> <em>King Josiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:26\">NEH 9:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:18\">DAN 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:20-Zech8:22\">ZEC 8:20–8:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:16\">MAL 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>In the NT</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:22-Acts11:23\">ACT 11:22–11:23</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:11-1Thess2:12\">1TH 2:11–2:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:36\">ACT 4:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:43\">ACT 13:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:21-Acts14:22\">ACT 14:21–14:22</a> <em>Paul and Barnabas</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:32\">ACT 15:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:40\">ACT 16:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:27-Acts18:28\">ACT 18:27–18:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:1-Acts20:2\">ACT 20:1–20:2</a> <em>after Paul's ministry in Ephesus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:11-Rom1:12\">ROM 1:11–1:12</a> <em>Paul to the church at Rome</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:4\">2CO 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:13\">2CO 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:21-Eph6:22\">EPH 6:21–6:22</a> <em>Paul's fellow-worker, Tychicus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:14\">PHP 1:14</a> <em>Paul in prison</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:8\">COL 4:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:2\">1TH 3:2</a> <em>Timothy</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:7\">1TH 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:7\">PHM 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:22\">HEB 13:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:12\">1PE 5:12</a></p>\n<h2>Encouragement as exhortation in the life of faith</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:28\">COL 1:28</a></strong> <em>Paul describes his ministry.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:18\">LUK 3:18</a> <em>John the Baptist</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:30\">ROM 15:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:16\">1CO 4:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:15-1Cor16:16\">1CO 16:15–16:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:7-2Cor2:8\">2CO 2:7–2:8</a> <em>dealing with a repentant member</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:1\">2CO 6:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:1\">EPH 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:10\">1TH 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:19\">HEB 13:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:3\">JUD 1:3</a></p>\n<h2>Commands to encourage others</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:3-Isa35:4\">ISA 35:3–35:4</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:38\">DEU 1:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:28\">DEU 3:28</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:7\">2SA 19:7</a> <em>to David</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:17\">ISA 1:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:6-Rom12:8\">ROM 12:6–12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:2\">ROM 15:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:12\">1CO 14:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:18\">1TH 4:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:11\">1TH 5:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:14\">1TH 5:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:1\">1TI 5:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:2\">2TI 4:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus1:9\">TIT 1:9</a> <em>the church overseer</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:15\">TIT 2:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:13\">HEB 3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:25\">HEB 10:25</a></p>\n<h2>Failure to encourage</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:4\">EZK 34:4</a></strong> <em>Condemnation of Israel's leaders.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job16:2\">JOB 16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:20\">PSA 69:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:1\">ECC 4:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek16:49\">EZK 16:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:2\">ZEC 10:2</a></p>\n<h2>Refusing to be comforted</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:34-Gen37:35\">GEN 37:34–37:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:2\">PSA 77:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:15\">JER 31:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:18\">MAT 2:18</a></p>\n<h2>Scripture censures those who encourage others to do evil</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr22:2-2Chr22:3\">2CH 22:2–22:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:25\">2SA 11:25</a> <em>after David and Joab had arranged Uriah's death</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:5\">PSA 64:5</a> <em>evildoers</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:7\">ISA 41:7</a> <em>makers of idols</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:14\">JER 23:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:8\">JER 29:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:22-Ezek13:23\">EZK 13:22–13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:9-1Cor8:10\">1CO 8:9–8:10</a></p>",
